y(0) = \pi
C = 2\pi
 \frac {dy}{dx} = \frac {e^x + x}{\sin y + 2} \\ (\sin y + 2) dy = (e^x + x) dx \\ \int (\sin y + 2) dy = \int (e^x + x) dx \\ -\cos y + 2y = e^x + \frac {x^2}2 + C 
 1 + 2\pi = 1 + C 
y(0) = \pi
 2y - \cos y = e^x + \frac {x^2}2 + 2\pi 
 \frac{dy}{dx} =\frac{e^x+x}{\sin y+2}=F(x,y).
F_y=\frac{\partial F}{\partial y}
